---
description: Use Bun instead of Node.js, npm, pnpm, vite
globs: "*.ts, *.tsx, *.html, *.css, *.js, *.jsx, package.json"
alwaysApply: false
---

Default to using Bun instead of Node.js.

- Use `bun run <script>` instead of `npm run` or `pnpm run`
- Use `bun install` instead of `npm install` or `pnpm install`
- Use `bun test` instead of `jest` or `vitest`
- Use `bunx <pkg> <cmd>` instead of `npx <pkg> <cmd>`
- Use `bun <file>` instead of `node <file>` or `ts-node <file>`
- Bun loads `.env` automatically; avoid dotenv
- Use `bun-types` in tsconfig for Bun APIs; extend `@workspace/typescript-config/bun.json` for API/CLI apps
